examples.en: It's difficult to avoid stepping on her sensitive feelings.
Modelling is seen as a stepping stone to a career in movies.
Trade has been stepping up recently.
I must be stepping. It's getting late.
She is always stepping on others to get ahead
Thanks for stepping into the breach last week.
She's really stepping out these days, isn't she?
She took a small jump forward to avoid stepping in the puddle.
No one told him that she had been stepping out on him for over a year.
The health department is stepping up efforts to reduce teenage smoking.
He took a deep breath to fortify himself before stepping onto the stage.
If she catches him stepping out on her, she'll divorce him without a moment's hesitation.
After stepping out of their hired limousine, the prom couple made a theatrical entrance in their evening clothes.
...the oft-told story of the foxy flatterer who works her way up the ladder of success by stepping on people as she goes...
